app

Class JCAT

  • java.lang.Object
    • app.JCAT

  • public class JCAT
extends java.lang.Object
    JCAT.java Define global constants All classes should use these definitions to reduce coupling to a single point. XML elements and attribute names should be defined here. Some naming conventions: 1. Write = Write information to a file 2. Send = Send information in a telemetry packet 3. cFE default file names are log and dat and the distinction is not clear. Table dump files are .dmp. No binary vs text convention. 4. The term 'core' has been used to go beyond the cFE and include items the user should not have to install. For example CI and TO lab.
    Author:
    David McComas
